Day 1 of the #AmiguruMay challenge— Hello AmiguruMay! I can’t believe it’s already May again! This is one of my favorite challenges and I’ve been looking forward to it all year! I’ve been taking a bit of a break from creating content and now is the perfect time to get back on track. But my favorite part of AmiguruMay? Finding new friends! If you’re participating, I can’t wait to see all of your responses to the prompts! And as always thank you to @airali_gray for hosting this challenge and inspiring all of us to push ourselves! 
Pattern: The Sun, the Moon, and the Stars by Me
Yarn: Caron One Pound

Day 2 of the #AmiguruMay challenge— My Amigurumi! Last year my book of patterns Crochet Magical Creatures came out, and it was definitely one of the highest points of my Amigurumi journey. There may be a few things I would change if I could, but that doesn’t stop me from being immensely proud of all 20 patterns in the book. Writing a book was a dream that I didn’t think would come true for many years and I am so grateful and lucky to have had it happen when it did. Thank you so much to everyone who has made something from the book and shared it with me, it fills my heart to the absolute brim! 
.
.
.
.
.

Day 3 of the #AmiguruMay challenge— Photo or video? After the past few years I definitely have to choose video. I’ve never been very good at saying everything I want to in a still photo, and with video you can really let loose and have fun with it. It also shows off your personality better (even if you’re not on screen!) It also adds a new layer of audio which opens up some many doors for expressing yourself! Plus I just have fun making them! 😅
Pattern: Mütiges Regenbogenmädchen from Helden der Kindheit 5
Yarn: Impeccable by Loops & Thread from @michaelsstores

[GIVEAWAY CLOSED- Winner will be announced Sunday Nov 12th]STELLA LIGHT GIVEAWAY!!! (US only🇺🇸)
First of all thank you so much to Stella for sending me this gorgeous Stella Two light- I can’t imagine creating content without it! Whether it’s making sure I have the best possible lighting for my pattern photos, or making sure everything looks perfect when I’m live streaming or filming videos, this light has been an absolute lifesaver!!! It’s designed to be used for good chunks of time without ever getting hot, it comes with several different modes of light as well as adjustable brightness. It is seriously so helpful!!!
I am teaming up with the wonderful people over at Stella to give one of these gorgeous lights away!
💡HOW TO WIN 💡
💡Follow me and @stellalighting and like this post
💡Tag a crafty friend who could use one of these gorgeous Lights! (Tag on friend per comment, multiple tags= multiple entries!
💡For an optional bonus entry share this post to your stories! (Be sure to tag me so I can see it!)
That’s it! Giveaway ends at 11:59pm EST on Saturday, November 11th, a winner will be selected and notified on Sunday, November 12th! 
Giveaway not affiliated with Instagram and is open to US residents only.
